#   SUBS-001: POST silently drops a level's own edits when its sub is also dirty (LANDED)

*HIGH ÔÇö silent data loss ÔÇö LANDED `97de77b8` (2026-06-06).*  Fixed per
option (a): `sniff/POST.c` `post_pd_cb` now classifies the auto-generated
sub-gitlink-bump `put <sub>#<40-hex>` row *before* the `c->any_pd = YES`
flip and returns early, so a dirty (or clean) sub no longer flips the level
into selective mode ÔÇö commit-all own-file edits survive.  Repros
`test/post/26` and `test/post/27` now pass (removed from `WILL_FAIL`).

*HIGH ÔÇö silent data loss.*  When a worktree level has BOTH its own dirty
tracked files AND a dirty mounted submodule, `be post` commits the gitlink
bump but *silently omits the level's own edits*, exiting 0.  Root cause: the
post-order recursion stages the sub's new tip with `be put <subpath>`, writing
a `put <subpath>#<sha>` row into `.be/wtlog`.  That lone explicit `put` row
flips the level's POST from *implicit (commit-all)* mode into *selective*
mode scoped to `<subpath>` only (see VERBS.md ┬º"Per-file classification"), so
the genuinely-dirty own files fall outside scope and never enter the commit.

##  Repro
 1. `be get <parent>?master` (parent has a `vendor/sub` gitlink).
 2. Append a line to `main.c` AND to `vendor/sub/core.c`.
 3. `be post 'both dirty'`.
 4. `be blob:main.c?master` ÔÇö the appended line is *absent*; exit was 0.

##  Manifestation B (only-parent-dirty ÔåÆ POSTNONE + sticky poison)
Edit only `main.c` (sub clean), `be post 'msg'`:
 -  Exit 206 POSTNONE; parent commit dropped, `main.c` edit uncommitted.
 -  The recursion still ran `be put vendor/sub` (staging the *unchanged* pin
    `put vendor/sub#<same-sha>`), flipping POST selective ÔåÆ the unchanged
    baseline resolves to no-change ÔåÆ POSTNONE.
 -  The stale put-row *persists* in `.be/wtlog`, so a follow-up
    `be post --nosub 'msg'` ALSO returns POSTNONE ÔÇö the parent stays stuck
    dropping its edits until the user manually runs `be put ./main.c`.

##  Expected
Commit-all (git `commit -a`) semantics for the level's own tracked files MUST
survive the sub-bump.  Per spec UC1/UC4: parent commit records BOTH `main.c`
and the gitlink bump; a clean sub no-ops without poisoning the parent commit.

##  Actual
Own edits dropped (exit 0, silent) when sub dirty; parent commit dropped
(POSTNONE) + sticky put-row when only parent dirty.  Confirmed at depth-3:
intermediate levels drop their own edits; only the leaf (no child sub) keeps
its own edit.

##  Root cause / fix sketch
The gitlink-bump put-row must not be treated as a *selective-mode trigger* for
the level's own commit-classification.  Options: (a) classify auto-generated
sub-bump `put` rows distinctly from user `put`s so they do not flip
implicitÔåÆselective; (b) when the only in-scope put rows are sub-gitlink bumps,
keep commit-all mode for the rest of the tree; (c) stage the sub bump as part
of the commit assembly rather than as a pre-POST `put` row.  Control proof:
`be post --nosub` commits `main.c` correctly (no sub put-row staged), pinning
the defect to the recursion's `bepost_bump_sub` step.

##  Tests
`test/post/26-sub-both-dirty-keeps-parent-edit` (manifestation A),
`test/post/27-sub-only-parent-dirty-commits` (manifestation B) ÔÇö both
`WILL_FAIL` until fixed.  Also covered end-to-end by `test/all/01-subs-all-verbs`.

